items.text: Putu mayam: Soon Huat Cooked Food (#01-71) is a nondescript stall sellg pineapple tarts & curry puffs. But main attraction is Putu Mayam, an Indian snack made of rice flour, served w palm sugar
Try the fishballs ... 6 for $1 .. Where to find !
Fresh pau (steamed dumpling), siew mai (pork dumpling) & mai kai (steamed glutinous rice + chicken) made on-d-spot @ Singapore Bao #01-61. Xpect q when demand outstrips supply (takes time 2 steam)
Must trys: carrot cake (near lor mee stall),  bak cho mee with fried wanton at "dhoby ghaut" stall at $2.50; under rated- Tasty and value for money. Finish by 1pm on wkends!
Yu tiao (fried dough fritters): Thick & substantial @ Eat May Know #01-32. Luv their caramelised butterfly fritters too. Join d q!
#01-65 YONG SIANG CHICKEN RICE is tempting the chilli is hot and tasty and the chicken is soft like the rice. Fav!
Shan Yuan Vegetarian at #01-41 is the best vegetarian stall here!
Sim's place prawn noodle.
Try the Sim's place pawn noodle here.. Yummy!!
Been loving this Rojak for more than 10 years. #01-32.
Breakfast over $2 white carrot cake and Kopi C $1
Min ji laksa!
Laksa: Lotsa stalls selling laksa but d specialist is Min Ji Laksa #01-31; it's all they sell. Katong laksa (more coconut milk) they r not, but their base packs a spicy punch! Generous ingredients
Sims Place Prawn Noodle rocks! Best prawn mee in Singapore! Order the soup version! Super thick and flavourful! :) If takeaway, the boss will pack the noodles separately!
Bak chok mee at AMIGO is da bomb!!! They are generous with crispy wanton and ingredients... run by friendly couple. My wkend delight! Stall located at a corner adjacent to the hainanese curry rice
The Carrot cake is great!
A cozy suburban hawker center that gets pretty crowded and during weekday lunch hour. Had a very satisfying, spicy and cheap bowl of laksa here.
Hai Sing Coffee nice!! The more sweet version superb!
For the famous Lor' Mee, the chances of you able to get it diminishes after 10am usually..
Chee cheong fun (rice rolls): Nan Rong has been selling here 4 as long as I can remember. Order with their yam cake, splash lotsa ti chiao (sweet bean sauce) & chilli, n u r all set 4 bfast
Sze chuan fish soup, fresh fish and savory soup, beancurd, sze chuan vegetables and a generous serving of green leafy vegetables adds variety to the bite, wholesome and healthy dish.
Come and try the 小碗面 here , comparing price , taste and portion 100% value for money... At $3.50 haha
Chee Cheong fun is the best :)
You guys gotta try the Ban Mian/E-Mian at the Ban Mian Yu Pian Tang store #01-62. The food is great and the friendly Uncle has a great smile! Enjoy!
My Sat breakfast must-have..... Lor Mee!! Super shiok!!
通宵潮洲鱼粥#01-14 in front of the carpark
The 'BENDEMEER HOT AND COLD DRINKS' stall at 1-48 sells REALLY THICK SOY MILK omg.
Try this out !:)
Seng Hin Coffee Stall serve the best coffee/tea/Milo. #01-18
Good local food with affordable price, yummy.
Yong Xiang carrot cake very nice. Must try! Stall no 01-35.
LUCKY economical fried beenhoon is awesome!!
I'm not a very oyster person but their oyster omelette is very addictive. (#01-01 后港福建面)
The laksa and fishball noodle at #01-33 is nice! Fav! :D
Spoilt for choices with the amazing array of mouth watering foods.
Fishball Noodle #01-50. The neighbourhood-favoured stall among the 3-4 offerings in the food centre. Fishballs are bouncy & chewy, chilli sauce packs a punch!
Vegetarian options: fried carrot cake, chee cheong fun, kueh, lontong, vegetarian bee hoon, yam cake, yong tau foo, prata, thosai, putu mayam, chwee kueh, peanut porridge, beancurd, pancake, yutiao
There's a famous '3-sisters' Wonton noodles
The #01-33 laksa soso. The other one nearby nicer :)
One of the best cleaner I've seen in Singapore. Cleans efficiently and polite. 👍👍👍
Soya milk shoot-out. Sampled (A) Min Hiang #01-60 & (B) Bendemeer Cold & Hot Drinks. B wins: thicker, can taste the soya. A tasted diluted
The cai png of stall #01-03 is awesome.
Samsui Woman Niang Dou Fu at #01-20 sells at 30c per piece!
Extremly good place for local food taste ! Not turistic at all! On the photo you'll find delicious coconut pankakes !
have 3 vegetarian food stall here. and none of them open at sunday....
The hokkien Mee at #01-30 deserves a 10x thumbs up!
Vegetarian Bee Hoon is still $2. Nice!
love the noodle!
What so good about the lor mee here. I stay here so long already never even like it at all. Try the wan ton mee instead.
Why are there no tips left for the Fishball Noodles? "Q"wy noodles, springy fish balls. Expect a long Q n closes by 12ish.
The fishbowl soup and carrot cake
Chung ping chicken rice 01-58 is tasty, nice chilli!
Wanton mee here is so nice ,specialist is cook by the boss(near to bak ku teh side)
Famous 真記香菇肉脞面 @ 01-21. Corner of the market nearest to the car park. Best!
Is the market open?
Sparse halal food choices.
Long Q during weekdays lunchtime.
Health Yong Tau Fu #01-34 Must Try!!!
Soya bean milk drink at 01-54 very nice :) thick, fragrant and not artificial :) must try.
Bak Kut Teh (pork ribs soup): Head 2 #01-23 for dis clear peppery soup. Order d spare ribs 4 best experience. They use fresh (vs frozen) meat. Burp!

Out of towners: here's that "local experience" you been craving. There's ~100 stalls and not a foreigner in sight. I followed the Tips to the Laksa (#33, pictured) and prawn noodles (#42). Both great.
Try the zi cha not bad ,value for money
Probably the best prata in the neighborhood but endure the seller's F-Up attitude.
Loving the min hiang soya bean + grass jelly drink.
try lucky teochew porridge (#01-36) if u r looking for home cooked food taste! 👍
Heng Kee Lor Mee #01-87 BEST! Don't need to come after 1000
Try the chicken chop here ! Nice n cheap :p
Try the rojak, best in my area so far
Yong tou hu fish ball best :)
Chwee kueh (steamed rice cakes). From Kovan Chwee Kueh #01-64). A light snack in the morning. Bite-size convenient for sharing too
Try the Zhen Ji Bak Chor Mee! Very nice!
Best laksa at the 01-33 .
Hainanese Porridge: Rare find in SG. Siang Kee Porridge #01-63. Rice grains not boiled in2 mush (like Cantonese 'chok'). Flavour options: fish, chicken, pork, century egg, cuttlefish, chicken egg
Can try e hup lee economical food stall
Rongxing fishball noodles has one of the longest q here. Got to get there before 12 or it will close by then! Sauce is just nice, fishballs are bouncy and fresh with springy noodles! Yums!
If you like your Lor Mee with lots of fried stuff then try it at Heng Kee Lor Mee at 01-87. The traditional Lor Mee has fish meat (not fried) and it balances the dish well.
Those who like prawn noodles should try Sims Place Prawn Noodle. The soup  base is very thick
Prawn noodles: What makes Sims Place #01-42 a memorable experience is d REALLY thick soup. Basic $3 order is served w pork ribs. 2 savour more, order a soup serving (2 get more of that flavour!)
Standard has dropped for Heng Lee Lor Mee.
Lor mee, prawn noodles, chicken rice, mincemeat noodles, duck rice
Try this stall Youtiao + Carrot cake!! They are superb nice!!
Healthy and delicious !variety of choices :) can try out !
Bak Chor mee (minced meat noodles): Reward urself w a bowl of generous portions of minced meat, stewed mushrooms & fried wantans, over springy cooked noodles. Zhen Ji (#01-21) far corner of d centre
The sugarcane juice at this stall is nice! #01-16
Beef noodle from Toa Payoh-Hwa Heng is good. Big portions, long queue!
Check out stall 01-29. 29 Delights. Tasty fish curry and sambal sotong.
Try Gao Ji fried bee hoon nice
Can Try 粥29湯 (Porridge & Soup) For Something Light. The Owner (think is husband n wife) they r super super v friendly
Lor mee: 2 stalls A (#01-87) & B (#01-39). A's sauce is thick, egg-y. Lots of crispy bits if u luv an oral party. B has freshly shredded fish meat & well-cooked braised pork slices
Heng kee lor mee so-so only
Try the fried bee hoon n noodle @ lucky  01-15..
Check out the Chee Cheong Fun, Economic Bee Hoon and Porridge at this stall (#01-56)!
괜찮아...there's a famous beef noodles stall
Sims Place Prawn Noodle must try! Have the traditional flavor, thick soup at reasonable price. Yummy
The laksa from #01-33 is delicious. The taste of the gravy is well balanced. Not too spicy, not too lemak. It's the old school type of laksa. The tau pok is yummy! Good value at S$3.00.
Lor mee is the win!
Chee Cheong fun is the best.. Must try!
The lor mee is a killer! After eating here, I can never find a place as good.
The ban mian is a must try!!
Tried e fish ban mien. It's light, fish is fresh. I'm not sure if it's a must try. Verdict is still out there.
Ice lemon tea sux
Chicken Wings at $1.20 each or 5pcs for 5$ is so yummy! :)
Fishball noodles: 2 popular stalls: #01-50 njoys d longer q, & new contender 01-72 (reportedly fr Margaret Drv) whose chilli is shiok! D other stalls not worth your palate's time
Heathy Yong tau foo, Margaret drive fish ball noodle and toa payoh beef noodle all great here
Fried carrot cake: 2 popular stalls: 1) Yong Xiang #01-35 & 2) Hai Sheng #01-85. 1 dish out old-skool style, where it's fried & cut in2 messy cubes. 2 pre-chunks, fries it flat w egg & is less salty
Indonesian curry rice sedap
Surprised that vegetarian stall Jian Kang #01-82 does not offer ur typical bee hoon fare. Instead they hv 'specials' like duck rice (very tasty), Lor Mee, Mee Siam, etc
The Indonesia curry rice is good... Don't miss this stall
Toa Payoh-Hwa Heng Beef Noodle #01-01. Very fresh beef and value for money.  Yummy.
Quote:"indonesian curry rice 印尼咖哩饭. Curry beef, kang kong + beef redang + stir fry dark soya sauce pork belly meat "
curry chicken quite decent here. but their plain rice can be better
The mee hoon kuey sucks!!
love the 雷茶饭 from vegeterian stall yummy
Surrounding kopitiams offer great alternative in the evening , for relaxing or watching soccer
沈氏坊蝦面，赞！:-P
Kopi: Of all d kopi stalls in d mkt, locals point out 2 fave brewers: Hin Lai #01-07 & Totally Coffee #01-73. After sampling most stalls, I totally agree! Fragrant & more importantly, strong stuff!
